from London to New York, Hong Kong closed down its international
airport Monday just after midnight and moved the contents 19 miles
west to a new $20 billion airport in time for the first flight to
land at 6:30 a.m. It is not the first time a city has switched
airports in a one-day move _ Denver and Munich, Germany, did it.
