   LIFESTYLE (``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ Hot, dry summer conditions are an
invitation to chinch bugs, and the typically hot and dry areas of
the lawn near the drive and street are especially vulnerable.
Chinch bugs suck the sap from grass blades and make them wilt, then
die. By KATHY HUBER.
</P>
<P>
   SANDALS (San Francisco) _ You know those suede, earth-bound
sandals that every Northern Californian owns? It turns out they
were fashionable nearly 10,000 years ago. Michael J. O'Brien, a
Louisiana State University anthropologist, says ``these shoes were
very stylish for the time.'' By CYNTHIA ROBINS.
</P>
