<P>
   ------------- Are men worth it? -------------
</P>
<P>
   More precisely, is the maxim true about marriage being good for
a man's health but hazardous for a woman's _ or is it a sly old
spinster's tale? Do women live better with men or without them, and
which life will be longer, and which will simply SEEM longer?
</P>
<P>
   Natalie Angier, a science writer for The New York Times, takes a
crack at answering these questions in a fascinating feature titled
``MEN. ARE WOMEN BETTER OFF WITH THEM, OR WITHOUT THEM?'' It is one
of NINE features from WOMEN'S HEALTH, an exclusive special section
from The New York Times that covers a range of health issues and
addresses every stage of a woman's life. The articles _ described
below _ are available for one-shot purchase from The New York Times
Syndicate.
</P>
