<SLUG> BC-POISONIVY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RASH JUDGMENT: A NEW LOTION PREVENTS POISON IVY ITCH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROLYN POIROT 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Leaves of three, let them be!
</P>
<P>
   Avoidance and protective clothing have long been the mainstays
for preventing poison ivy. But who really wants to wear long
sleeves, pants and gloves outdoors in the summer?
</P>
<P>
   Now, for the first time, a pre-exposure lotion has been approved
by the FDA for extra protection. IvyBlock, from EnviroDerm
Pharmaceuticals, is the first product on the market containing
bentoquatum, approved by the FDA to shield against poison ivy's
irritating oily sap.
</P>
<P>
   IvyBlock is an over-the-counter, nonprescription lotion that is
applied like sunscreen. It leaves a faint white coating on the skin
that acts as a barrier against the harmful oils in poison ivy, oak
and sumac.
</P>
<P>
   The lotion should be applied at least 15 minutes before possible
exposure and reapplied every four hours as needed.
</P>
<P>
   Its active ingredient, bentoquatum, is a claylike compound
mainly added to paints and lubricants to alter their flow. It is
used in eye shadows, lipsticks and suntan products.
</P>
<P>
   IvyBlock lotion is sold in 4-ounce squeeze bottles for $9 to $10
and is available at drug and general merchandise stores, including
Eckerd, Drug Emporium and Wal-Mart.
</P>
<P>
   Poison ivy is the most common cause of allergic contact
dermatitis in North America. Fifty to 70 percent of the population
is susceptible, said Dr. Joseph Fowler, associate clinical
professor of dermatology at the University of Louisville in
Kentucky, who conducted some of the trials on bentoquatum.
</P>
<P>
   IvyBlock was developed especially for people such as forest
firefighters, for whom poison ivy is an occupational hazard, Fowler
added.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-06-98 1319EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
