</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    RuPaul will warble for `Runway Hits'
 &HT;    By Russ Devault
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Rhino, the Los Angeles-based label that is the recording
industry's leading producer of compilation albums, tips its hat to
high fashion with ``Runway Hits.'' RuPaul's ``Supermodel (You
Better Work)'' is among the 18 tracks Rhino says have become
synonymous with fashion shows and the TV programs that touch on
them.
</P>
<P>
   Cuts include ``Free Your Mind'' by En Vogue, ``Simply
Irresistible'' by Robert Palmer, ``New Attitude'' by Patti LaBelle
and ``The Glamorous Life'' by Sheila E. It's due at retail next
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Armageddon'' soundtrack (Columbia). Grade: C-.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Cabaret _ The New Broadway Cast Recording'' (RCA Victor).
</P>
<P>
   -- barenaked ladies, ``Stunt'' (Reprise). Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   -- John Forte, ``Poly Sci'' (Ruffhouse/Columbia). Grade: C+.
</P>
<P>
   -- New Power Generation, ``New Power Soul'' (NPG Records).
Thinly disguised Prince/the Artist album. Grade: B-.
</P>
