BC-RODALE-BRIEFS-NYTSF).
</P>
<P>
   3. HEALTHY EATING: WHAT'S FRESH NOW, RASPBERRIES AND FIGS. From
Prevention with art. Raspberries and figs: sweet, nutritious and in
season. (slugged: BC-HEALTHY-EATING-NYTSF).
</P>
<P>
   4. TREATING LAZY EYE. From ``Keeping Kids Healthy.'' Amblyopia,
or lazy eye, is a fairly common vision problem that may affect as
many as three out every 100 people. Experts say early treatment by
an eye specialist is critical. (slugged:
BC-RODALE-HEALTHY-PARENTING-NYTSF).
</P>
<P>
   5. KEEPING FIT: TONE YOUR BODY WHILE YOU GLIDE AND PLAY. From
