<SLUG> BC-TV-SURFER07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Lovitz joins ``Newsradio'''s cast
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   As expected, former ``Saturday Night Live'' funnyman Jon Lovitz
will join the cast of NBC's ``NewsRadio'' this fall, playing a new
character to replace the late Phil Hartman.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm doing this for Phil,'' Lovitz told Variety. ``There's
nothing more to say.''
</P>
<P>
   Hartman was shot to death in his California home earlier this
year, apparently by his wife, who then committed suicide.
</P>
<P>
   ``The last time I talked to Phil, he called Jon 'the most
naturally funny' person he'd ever met,'' said ``NewsRadio'' creator
Paul Simms.
</P>
<P>
   ``From a creative standpoint, there was never any question about
Jon Lovitz being our first choice,'' added Brad Grey, executive
producer and chairman of Brillstein Grey Entertainment, which makes
``NewsRadio'' for NBC.
</P>
<P>
   Lovitz, who earlier this year starred in an ABC pilot that did
not get picked up for fall, will likely portray a character in the
``NewsRadio'' newsroom who was an old friend of Bill McNeal, the
role played by Hartman.
</P>
<P>
   The show's producers are reportedly considering having McNeal
pass away as an explanation for his absence.
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: channelsurfer(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
