for average-height Americans; rather, they are the emotional chasms
which need to be bridged to build relationships with taller folks,
according to participants at the Little People of America's 1998
National Conference in Woodland Hills. Actor Michael Gogin, who
appears in the feature film ``Fear and Loathing,'' tells of the
long road before his late mother-in-law finally accepted him and
told him she loved him. Gogin is married to an ``N.L.'' Gogin and
his son Matt, who also is a dwarf, are among the thousands of
little people at the national conference. By Doug Haberman. (Will
move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news file.) &QL;
