   &UR; IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Reading her SFMOMA newsletter,  &UR; Patti Itano &LR;  was delighted by
the description of the forthcoming show ``Do Normal,'' which comes
from a Dutch idiom that means ``act in a normal manner and you will
be weird enough.'' Who would have thought the Dutch could ``be so
very San Francisco with so little effort?'' she asks.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Andre Halaczkiewicz &LR;  came across  &UR; citybird.com,  &LR; a travel Web
site that advises San Francisco visitors to stop in at the City of
Paris department store (closed for more than 20 years), discover
the ``natural history'' museum the Exploratorium, and visit the
city's ``Irish quarter.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Watching the shooting of the  &UR; Robin Williams  &LR; movie ``What
