</HEADLINE>
  Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CNN-NERVE-GAS-NYT (moved on Thursday, July 2)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, July 2,
about CNN's retraction of its assertion that United States military
forces used nerve gas in 1970 misidentified the firm hired by the
lawyer Floyd Abrams to help him investigate the CNN report. The
firm is Kroll Associates, part of the Kroll-O'Gara Company; while
its chief executive is Jules Kroll, the firm does not bear his
name.
</P>
<P>
   BC-PATENTS-STATES-LAW-NYT (moved on Wednesday, July 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, July 1,
about a ruling that lets the College Savings Bank sue the State of
Florida in a patent infringement case misstated the amount of
profit that the bank contends Florida has made from the
unauthorized use of a college savings program. It is about a
quarter of a billion dollars, not a quarter of a million.
</P>
