<HEADLINE>
HOW WEB SAVVY ARE YOU? 
 &HT;      
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by clients of the New York Times News Service)   By Jamie Beckett  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL;
<P>
   Here are some questions _ all with answers on the Web _ from the
MCI Great American Net Test. Answers and Web sources are at the
bottom.
</P>
<P>
   1) What was Houdini's birth name?
</P>
<P>
   A. Ehrich Weiss
</P>
<P>
   B. Erik Weisz
</P>
<P>
   C. Theodore Wiess
</P>
<P>
   D. Eric Steiner
</P>
<P>
   E. Samuel Mayer
</P>
<P>
   2) In what year does Emily Bronte's Wuthering Heights begin?
</P>
<P>
   A. 1797
</P>
<P>
   B. 1801
</P>
<P>
   C. 1803
</P>
<P>
   D. 1807
</P>
<P>
   E. 1812
</P>
<P>
   3) New York City's Chrysler Building was designed by
</P>
<P>
   A. Raymond Hood
</P>
<P>
   B. Daniel Burnham
</P>
<P>
   C. Craig Severance
</P>
<P>
   D. Shreve, Lamb, and Harmon
</P>
<P>
   E. William van Alen
</P>
<P>
   4) What is the key of Beethoven's Sixth Symphony, ``Pastorale?''
</P>
<P>
   A. C-Major
</P>
