<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-SOUTHCAROLINA-GAYS-NYT, which
moved in ``a'' news file.) 
c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``People here perceive themselves on the defensive, defending
their culture, their religion, their communities, against outside
forces. They see these changes, such as homosexuality, and they
rebel.''
</P>
<P>
   _CHARLES W. DUNN, a political scientist at Clemson University.
</P>
</TEXT>
