<HEADLINE>
MOTHER IS ACCUSED OF NEGLECT 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 By AMY WALDMAN   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A Brooklyn woman was charged with child endangerment
Monday after police officers responding to a domestic dispute found
her three children unkempt and without food in a dirty apartment.
</P>
<P>
   A Police Department spokesman, Cadet Donald Stewart, said
officers responded to a dispute Monday morning at 183 Menahan St.,
in the Bushwick section, where they found a man having seizures.
After calling for an ambulance for the man, who was not related to
anyone in the apartment, the officers saw the squalid conditions in
the apartment and found the children _ a girl, 8, and two boys,
ages 1 and 6, Stewart said. The year-old boy, he said, had been
wearing a dirty diaper for ``a long period of time.''
</P>
<P>
   The officers arrested the children's mother, Carmen Burnes, 31,
who was charged with endangering the welfare of a child. The
children were taken to Wyckoff Heights Medical Center, where they
were examined and released to the custody of the Administration for
Children's Services.
</P>
<P>
   Leonora Wiener, a spokeswoman for the agency, said officials
were checking the agency's records to see if Ms. Burnes had a
history of abuse or neglect. She said the children would be placed
in foster care.
</P>
</TEXT>
